I got Little J â€˜s favourite Japanese Strawberries ğŸ“ğŸ“ from @isetansg and they are so sweet and juicy ! Isetan is my to go supermarket whenever I am in Orchard!

I love their fresh and wide range of Japanese products! I love their vibrant Japanese culture thereğŸ˜ 

Isetan will celebrate its 50th anniversary this year. 
Isetan supermarket is well known for its fine and fresh Japanese food, there you could find Japanese food treasures. 
I always find my â€œ treasures there!â€ Foodstuffs that I used to find in Japan 

Isetan is known for these:
Vegetable
The seasonal fresh vegetable and fruis are brought by air 4 times a week.
Now it is a season of Fresh Strawberries! ğŸ“ğŸ“

Egg
The Mangetsu pasteurized eggs are well loved for those who love the raw eggs. 
Japanese have a food culture to eat egg as raw such as Tamagokakw goban (literally just cup of rice topped on raw egg!) 

Wagyu
Wagyu are from Tochigi, Saga and Sendai from Japan. 
Wagyu is quite popular among Isetan customers. 

Rice
There are more than 20 kind of Japanese rice all the time. 
Japanese rice is good for making Sushi-rice. 

Sauce dressing 
Isetan has a wide range of Japanese sauce and dressing.
Pounzu, wasabi based and Japanese Worcestershire sauce etc 
You will never get bored to explore its collection!

Fish
There is a Japanese chef who takes care of preparing sashimi & sushi etc.
If you buy blocks of sashimi, you could ask chef to slice them as you like!

Tomiz Corner 
There is a corner of Japanese baking ingredients section by Tomiz.
Tomiz is well known as Tomizawa Shoten, a provider of all sort of baking ingredients. For baking lover like me â¤ï¸

Visit https://www.instagram.com/isetansg/Supermarket

Simply easy to make this pot of goodness. 

ğŸŒŸMix 4TbspÂ Korean chili flakesÂ (Gochugaru), 4 TbspÂ mirin, 2TbspÂ soy sauce, 2Tbsp minced garlic, 1Tbsp sugar, 3TbspÂ Korean chili pasteÂ (Gochujang)and a few sprinkles of ground black pepper in small bowl. You can adjust based on your preferance for the sauce.

ğŸŒŸAll you need is to assemble the ingredients including the sauce (except for instant ramen noodles, rice cakes, chopped chilies ğŸŒ¶ & green onion and cheese ğŸ§€) in the pot. 

ğŸŒŸPour in homemade 1.5litre chicken stock and let it boil for about 10 mins. Once boil, add it instant ramen noodles, rice cakes, green onion and cheese to cook for about 2 mins. Lower heat if you are using portable burner and Enjoy! We cooked in a claypot  to keep the food warm while enjoying on dining table.
